If you want to see the funny math symbolsin the definition of an invertible function:

f invertible ⇔ ∃!x∈X: y=f(x) ∀y∈Y.

&quot;⇔&quot; is &quot;if and only if&quot;
&quot;∃!&quot; is &quot;there exists unique&quot;
&quot;:&quot; is &quot;such that&quot;
&quot;∀&quot; is &quot;for all&quot;
&quot;∈&quot; is &quot;member of&quot; or &quot;in&quot;

Another way to say this is that f is invertible iff f is bijective.
Bijective is just a single word for surjective AND injective.
